      <byline class="print_byline">By LIBRADO ROMERO</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Photo of character in movie Shaft being tossed from office window in Times Square in New York City</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Filmmakers have always loved Times Square. The visual and moral fabric of the area in the late 1960s and early '70s was captured in films like John Schlesinger's ''Midnight Cowboy'' (1969) and Martin Scorsese's ''Taxi Driver'' (1976). For his 1971 movie ''Shaft,'' the director Gordon Parks had the Shaft character toss a hoodlum from a Times Square office window.</p>
      </block>
